Running command: cat > reproduce_issue.py << 'PY'
# Reproduction script for method string handling
# Shows difference between builtin_str (str) and to_native_string
import sys, os
sys.path.insert(0, os.path.join(os.getcwd(), 'requests'))
from requests.compat import builtin_str
from requests.utils import to_native_string

b = b'GET'
print('builtin_str(b):', builtin_str(b))
print('to_native_string(b):', to_native_string(b))

# Expectation: builtin_str(b) == "b'GET'" but to_native_string(b) == 'GET'
if builtin_str(b) == to_native_string(b):
    print('No difference detected')
    sys.exit(1)
else:
    print('Difference detected as expected')
    sys.exit(0)
